description: A hunter, a baseball player and an astronomer are abducted by the Reynans. Captain Comet discerns that all of the abductees had keen eyesight. The Reynans come for Captain Comet. Rather than resist, Captain Comet allows himself to be abducted by the Reynans. Captain Comet learns, telepathically, that, due to the radiation emitted by a super nova, the Reynans are going blind. The Reynans have been abducting human beings with perfect eyesight to serve as their guides. Upon reaching the Reynan home world, and finding the other abductees, Captain Comet escapes his bonds. Captain Comet rescues the abductees. Captain Comet declares that a civilization, one as advanced as the Reynans, should be able to learn to compensate for their disability.
name: The Seeing Eye Humans

description:
The Syndicate Strikes

Justice... the magazine criminals fear... scores another victory over crime in this authentic expose of the most rotten business in the world... and what happens when... The Syndicate Strikes

Jail Break!

Justice... the magazine dedicated to fight against crime.. brings to its readers another exclusive story taken from the files of a large Midwestern penitentiary! Justice Magazine extends grateful appreciation to the warden without whose cooperation this true-life account would not have been possible... Jail Break!

The Swindler (Text Only Story)

The Big Blowup!

Back in the 1930's, one man alone could claim the title of kingpin of the safe-crackers in England! His name was Jerry Dukes... his specialty was blowing the doors off safes and vaults... his methods... the most daring to ever challenge the police officials of two countries!

Shark Bait

The scene below took place before the turn of the century, off San Francisco between a cargo vessel and the immigration police on a Harbor Patrol boat! We who live in America don't realize that many people have paid a high price to enter this country! Sometimes they even paid with their lives!

"The Guilty Gorilla," by writer John Broome and artist Murphy Anderson is a foray into the intelligent Gorilla craze that flourished in the DC line of comics during the 1950s. In this issue, Captain Comet took a break from his usual interplanetary adventures and stayed home in Midway City to break up a criminal syndicate run by a super gorilla.
name: The Guilty  Gorilla
